In this contest Cloanthus received a cloak embroidered with gold ς Mnestheus, a corslet 3 Gyas,¹ a pair of brazen cauldrons and drink- ing cup. Sergestus who ran his ship aground received a consola- tion prize of a female slave and twin babes. (2) The foot-race (285·361) in which Euryalus gains the first prize3 Helymus. the second, and Dares, third ; Salius and Nisus follow. All receive a pair of Cretan arrows and an axe, but the first receives in addition a horse with trappings ; the second, a quiver full of arrows; the third, an Argive helmet. Salius receives a lion's skin, and Nisus a shield, as consolation prizes.
